            <thetext>The developer should be able to define

- an event type to check for
- a selector to match the event target
- a callback to execute
- an optional callback context

With this information it is possible to use a shortcut for the use case when an event target has to be checked. 

E.g. a popup is shown and the developer wants to hide this popup whenever the user clicked somewhere else.</thetext>
